# 25 Most Dangerous Kubernetes Production Failures

*(with exact kubectl troubleshooting commands)*

---

# 1. Entire Application Down

### Symptoms

Users cannot access application.

### First Commands Senior Engineers Run

```bash
kubectl get nodes
kubectl get pods -A
kubectl get svc -A
```

### What They Check

* Node status
* Pods running
* Service endpoints

---

# 2. All Pods Restarting

### Symptoms

Pods continuously restarting.

### Debug

```bash
kubectl get pods
kubectl describe pod <pod>
kubectl logs <pod> --previous
```

### Root Causes

* App crash
* Environment variable missing
* Database connection failure

---

# 3. CrashLoopBackOff Storm

### Debug

```bash
kubectl get pods
kubectl describe pod <pod>
kubectl logs <pod>
```

### Fix

* Fix environment variables
* Correct configmap/secrets
* Fix application error

---

# 4. Node Suddenly NotReady

### Debug

```bash
kubectl get nodes
kubectl describe node <node>
```

### Senior Engineer Action

SSH into node

```bash
systemctl status kubelet
systemctl restart kubelet
```

---

# 5. All Pods Stuck Pending

### Debug

```bash
kubectl get pods
kubectl describe pod <pod>
```

### Causes

* Cluster resource exhaustion
* Node selector mismatch
* Taints

---

# 6. ImagePullBackOff During Production Deploy

### Debug

```bash
kubectl describe pod <pod>
```

### Causes

* Wrong image tag
* Registry authentication issue

---

# 7. Service Suddenly Not Working

### Debug

```bash
kubectl get svc
kubectl get endpoints
kubectl get pods --show-labels
```

### Cause

Service selector mismatch.

---

# 8. LoadBalancer No External IP

### Debug

```bash
kubectl get svc
kubectl describe svc <service>
```

### Cause

Cloud provider issue.

---

# 9. DNS Failure Between Services

### Debug

```bash
kubectl exec -it <pod> -- nslookup service-name
```

### Senior Fix

Restart DNS

```bash
kubectl rollout restart deployment coredns -n kube-system
```

---

# 10. Persistent Volume Not Mounting

### Debug

```bash
kubectl get pvc
kubectl describe pvc <pvc>
kubectl get pv
```

### Cause

Storage class issue.

---

# 11. Pods Evicted

### Debug

```bash
kubectl describe pod <pod>
```

### Cause

Node resource pressure.

---

# 12. High CPU Causing Application Failure

### Debug

```bash
kubectl top pods
kubectl top nodes
```

### Fix

Scale deployment

```bash
kubectl scale deployment app --replicas=5
```

---

# 13. Memory OOMKilled Containers

### Debug

```bash
kubectl describe pod <pod>
```

Look for

```
OOMKilled
```

### Fix

Increase memory limits.

---

# 14. Deployment Rollout Stuck

### Debug

```bash
kubectl rollout status deployment app
kubectl describe deployment app
```

### Emergency Fix

Rollback

```bash
kubectl rollout undo deployment app
```

---

# 15. Ingress Returning 404

### Debug

```bash
kubectl get ingress
kubectl describe ingress
```

### Cause

Path routing misconfiguration.

---

# 16. TLS Certificate Expired

### Debug

```bash
kubectl describe ingress
```

### Fix

Renew certificate.

---

# 17. ConfigMap Change Not Applied

### Debug

Pods still using old config.

### Fix

Restart pods

```bash
kubectl rollout restart deployment app
```

---

# 18. Secrets Not Mounted

### Debug

```bash
kubectl describe pod
```

Check volume mounts.

---

# 19. API Server Slow

### Debug

```bash
kubectl get componentstatuses
kubectl get pods -n kube-system
```

---

# 20. etcd Disk Full

### Symptoms

Cluster stops responding.

### Debug

Check etcd pod

```bash
kubectl get pods -n kube-system
```

---

# 21. Scheduler Not Scheduling Pods

### Debug

```bash
kubectl logs -n kube-system kube-scheduler-<node>
```

---

# 22. RBAC Permission Denied

### Debug

```bash
kubectl auth can-i create pods
```

### Fix

Update role binding.

---

# 23. Pod Stuck Terminating

### Debug

```bash
kubectl get pod
```

### Fix

Force delete

```bash
kubectl delete pod <pod> --grace-period=0 --force
```

---

# 24. Namespace Stuck Terminating

### Cause

Finalizers.

### Fix

Remove finalizer manually.

---

# 25. Production Deployment Broke Everything

### Symptoms

After deployment → site down.

### Senior Engineer Action

Immediately rollback

```bash
kubectl rollout undo deployment app
```

